This paper deals with the performance analysis of wireless networks, specifically cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of transmission schemes to achieve a certain throughput, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with the issue of interference, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses a fluid model to analyze the delay-throughput tradeoff, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the coexistence of two wireless networks, which is a topic in cognitive radio (cs.CR).
